Extract ALL attendees from the calendar event (excluding the current user/organizer).

INPUT: <event>{{processed_gcal_event}}</event>

Organizer domain: {{processed_gcal_event.event.organizer.domain}}

Classify each attendee as internal (same email domain as organizer) or external (different email domain).

DO NOT try to infer company names from domains - the Contact Research Agent will handle that.
Just extract the raw name and email exactly as they appear on the calendar invite.

OUTPUT (JSON):
{
  "external_attendees": [
    {"name": "string (exactly as shown on invite)", "email": "string"}
  ],
  "internal_attendees": [
    {"name": "string", "email": "string"}
  ],
  "metadata": {
    "total_external": "number",
    "total_internal": "number",
    "organizer_domain": "string"
  }
}

Summarize the internal team members joining this meeting (no deep research needed).

INTERNAL ATTENDEES:
{{classified_attendees.internal_attendees}}

SELLER CONTEXT (if available):
{{seller_context}}

USER INFO:
{{user.context.first_name}} {{user.context.last_name}} ({{_google_email}})

For each internal attendee:
1. Parse their name from email if name not provided (e.g., chris.b@mail.agent.ai → Chris B.)
2. If they match the seller/user context, note their role
3. Keep it brief - just name and inferred role

OUTPUT (JSON):
{
  "internal_team_summary": {
    "count": "number",
    "team_members": [
      {"name": "string", "email": "string", "role": "Meeting organizer | Internal attendee | Host"}
    ],
    "note": "Brief note about team composition if relevant (e.g., Large internal team suggests important meeting)"
  }
}
